review_blob: Very nice aroma, and a nice, full taste from this bock beer. A Texas classic.
Better than Corona, without all the overpriced hype. A very drinkable lager, but nothing special.
This will receive ones across the board. The only reason it get a higher score overall is due to the cheap price and only having 64 calories.
Not much to look at appearance wise, this pours similar to a cheaper lager. The taste completely makes up for this, with a cool, crisp finish.
Dont see what the hype about this is. It is a very decent beer, but is way overpriced.
A quite nice looking beer, only fails on taste. That is relative, however, as I would agree that this is a very underrated beer.
A horrendous piss-like brew. Only suitable for fraternities or those otherwise completely out of money. It only gets more points overall for being cheap.
Probably one of the best "mass-produced" beers available. Always has a good poor, with a nice dark appearance to it.

Much worse than the slightly older OB Blue. A pathetic attempt at a German-style lager. A truly pretentious beer if there ever was one.

The pour is awful, with almost no head. The taste is surprisingly bitter, but not in a good way as if drinking a delicious pale ale. Bottle or tap does not make a difference. Overall all I give this beer a 1 for pretentious advertising out of its class, being overpriced for what it is, and of course for tasting like absolute garbage. Please bring back OB Blue, for even though it was cheap "Bud-like" beer, it was drinkable and it was what it meant to be.

Worse than Bud. Promoted as if on a higher level, to perhaps Heineken, but actually more like old Keystone light. Just look at the deScription - "Cass is a most distinguished lager beer." It is only distinguished by the blatant odors of corn and iron emanating from this beer upon opening. The appearance is of a somewhat darker urine, hence the 2 star rating there.

Drinkable only if ice cold and for the sole purpose of getting a hangover. Stay clear of this one if possible...
